setup a Splunk HTTP Event Collector. Please refer to the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/latest/Data/UsetheHTTPEventCollector"
      }}>{`Splunk setup
docs`}</a>{` for a guide on how to do this. Once you've setup
your Spunk HTTP Collectory you'll be provided a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#host"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`host`}</inlineCode></a>{` and `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#token"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`token`}</inlineCode></a>{` that you
should supply to the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#host"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`host`}</inlineCode></a>{` and `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#token"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`token`}</inlineCode></a>{` options.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "tls-1"
